headline: DuPont Agrees to Divest Its Aramids Business to Arclin for $1.8B
summary: DD is set to sell its Kevlar and Nomex Aramids business to Arclin in a $1.8 billion deal, sharpening its focus and strengthening its financial profile.

headline: Zacks.com featured highlights include Vertiv Holdings, The Progressive, Bank OZK, TransUnion and The Mosaic
